                    "company": "Maastricht University",
                    "description": "As a Marie Curie Fellow, I'm studying the organisational structure and legal aspects of early modern private partnerships in the Meuse-Rhine region. The research aims at identifying the various types of private partnerships, as well as their distinctive features, that can be qualified as customary within the cities of Maastricht, Aachen and Li\u00e8ge. In addition, I'm striving for a reconstruction and description of the most elementary aspects of early modern company law as it was perceived and actually applied by the merchants and craftsmen of the respective cities. In order to do so, the research is primarily based on a profound and comparative analysis of numerous partnership agreements that can be found in the notarial archives of the aforementioned cities.\nIn a second stage, the results of the archival research will be interpreted against the background of the internationally, heavily debated topics of the myth of the customary law merchant, or so-called 'lex mercatoria', and their role in the emergence of capitalist rationality in the early modern period.",
                    "title": "Marie Curie Fellow",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
